\par Welcome to Actor, a program designed to analysis input sentences entered by the user
 and generate reply sentences based on that analysis.  To put it another way, you type a sentence and the actor replies.  For a more extended description, see the next section.  There is a sample actor in the distribution called Alice which you might want
 to load to have a small initial working vocabulary.
\par 
\par Since this is an alpha release, the most helpful thing you could do for me is bash it about a bit and tell me exactly when it begins to plead for mercy (i.e. crashes).  Naturally, the more details you ca
n provide me with what you did to cause any crash, the better.  Stability is the priority.
\par 
\par Having said that, it seems reasonably stable at the moment but to be honest, I haven't really destruction tested it - I wanted to at least get an initial release ou
t to you select people :-)  So if you do have fun with it, don't trust it too much with any vocabulary files.  Although I'll try to maintain compatability between vocabulary files saved using different versions, I can't guarantee this.
\par 
\par Also give me any su
ggestions about what else you think the program should do would be appreciated, what features of the user interface you find annoying, etc.  It would be great to get this kind of feedback.  Give me a mail too if you want to know more about how the program
 exactly works - I may not yet have explained it particularly well or comprehensively.
\par 
\par Please excuse the primitive documentation.  Over releases this should improve - I might even get round to writing a proper help file!
